#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn4.7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.7:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. Life Span "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 7. Supatisutta → soppasisuttaṃ (bj) | suppatisuttaṃ (s1-3) | suppati (pts1)
msgctxt "sn4.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Supatisutta "
msgstr "7. Sleeping "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn4.7:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.7:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bahudevarattiṃ abbhokāse caṅkamitvā rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ pāde pakkhāletvā vihāraṃ pavisitvā "
msgstr "He spent most of the night practicing walking meditation in the open. At the crack of dawn he washed his feet and entered his dwelling. "

msgctxt "sn4.7:1.3"
msgid "dakkhiṇena passena sīhaseyyaṃ kappesi pāde pādaṃ accādhāya sato sampajāno uṭṭhānasaññaṃ manasi karitvā. "
msgstr "He laid down in the lion’s posture—on the right side, placing one foot on top of the other—mindful and aware, and focused on the time of getting up. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.7:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked went up to the Buddha and addressed him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.240, sc2
msgctxt "sn4.7:2.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ soppasi kiṃ nu soppasi, "
msgstr "“What, you’re asleep? Really, you’re asleep? "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: dubbhago → dubbhato (s1-3, km) | dubbhayo (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn4.7:2.2"
msgid "Kimidaṃ soppasi dubbhago viya; "
msgstr "You sleep like a loser—what’s up with that? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.7:2.3"
msgid "Suññamagāranti soppasi, "
msgstr "You sleep, thinking that the hut is empty. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.7:2.4"
msgid "Kimidaṃ soppasi sūriye uggate”ti. "
msgstr "You sleep when the sun has come up—what’s up with that?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn4.7:3.1"
msgid "“Yassa jālinī visattikā, "
msgstr "“For them there is no craving—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.7:3.2"
msgid "Taṇhā natthi kuhiñci netave; "
msgstr "the weaver, the clinger—to lead them anywhere. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.7:3.3"
msgid "Sabbūpadhiparikkhayā buddho, "
msgstr "With the ending of all attachments the awakened Buddha sleeps. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.7:3.4"
msgid "Soppati kiṃ tavettha mārā”ti. "
msgstr "What’s that got to do with you, Māra?” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn4.7:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā … pe … tatthevantaradhāyīti. "
msgstr "Then Māra … vanished right there."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
